        {
          "aiAppOutputSpecification": {
            "dataDisplay": {
              "layouts": [
                "ORA_LAYOUT_MESSAGES_LIST"
              ],
              "enableActions": false,
              "enableCommunications": false,
              "customNotes": "ROOT CONFIGURATION:\n\n1. `title`: Do not include any title.\n2. `subtitle`: Map to `Current Rating: {$context.$nodes.FETCH_RISK_OF_LOSS_DETAILS_FOR_PERSON.$output}`.\n3. `summary`: Write exactly 3 bullet points. Each bullet must describe the Risk of Loss assessment using the provided `RiskOfLoss` and `RiskOfLossNumericRating` values only as internal evidence. Do not show numeric values in the visible output.\n4. `badgeText`: Do not include a badge.\n5. `priority`: Map to `alert`, `warning`, `medium`, or `success` based on the Risk of Loss severity.\n\nSTRICT MAPPING RULES:\n\n1. Use only the provided JSON from `{{$context.$nodes.FETCH_RISK_OF_LOSS_DETAILS_FOR_PERSON.$output}}`.\n2. Extract only the following identity fields for traceability: `DisplayName`, `PersonId`, and `AssignmentId`.\n3. Read the current Risk of Loss rating from `directsTalentRatings.items[0].RiskOfLoss`.\n4. Read the current Risk of Loss numeric rating from `directsTalentRatings.items[0].RiskOfLossNumericRating` only to determine severity.\n5. Do not infer protected attributes.\n6. Do not treat Potential as Risk of Loss.\n7. Do not speculate beyond what is present in the JSON.\n8. Do not show any numeric values in the visible output.\n9. Do not skip the subtitle.\n10. Do not include any extra text outside the requested JSON-like content.\n\nSEVERITY LOGIC:\n\n1. Normalize the rating label by lowercasing, trimming whitespace, removing punctuation, and collapsing repeated spaces.\n2. Use the normalized `RiskOfLoss` and `RiskOfLossNumericRating` to determine severity.\n3. Sort or interpret severity from lowest risk to highest risk when comparing multiple entries.\n4. Map severity to priority as follows:\n\n   * `success`: very low, low, minimal, unlikely, stable, not at risk\n   * `medium`: moderate, medium, watch, elevated, some risk\n   * `warning`: high, very high, at risk\n   * `alert`: critical, imminent, severe, highest risk\n5. If the rating scale is non-standard, infer the closest severity only from the provided label and numeric rating.\n\nACTION LOGIC:\n\n1. Do not include an `action` property unless the input explicitly provides one.\n2. If an action is provided, map it using `ora.Invoke(\"command\")` or `ora.Invoke(\"command\", \"{contextData}\")`.\n3. If context is needed for follow-up processing, include only the identifiers or state required for the next step.\n\nOUTPUT REQUIREMENTS:\n\n1. Produce one `messageListWidget` item per employee record.\n2. For each item, use:\n\n   * `items[].title`: Do not give any title.\n   * `items[].subtitle`: `Current Rating: {RiskOfLoss}`\n   * `items[].summary`: 3 concise bullet-style lines about risk evidence and calibration context. USE bullet points for this.\n   * `items[].priority`: severity-based color mapping\n   * `items[].timestamp`: leave blank unless explicitly provided\n   * `items[].badgeText`: omit\n3. Keep the tone professional, calibration-focused, and evidence-based.\n4. Do not output any content that is not part of the requested mapped result.\n\n** FINAL OUTPUT RULE:\n * Return ONLY a single <oraInfoDisplay> XML block and NOTHING ELSE.\n * No trailing text. No leading text. No explanations."
            }
          },
